Uchumi Supermarkets of Kenya Full-Year Profit Falls 55% as Costs Increase

-- B y   P a u l   R i c h a r d s o n
-- 
2011-09-09T04:31:27Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-09/uchumi-supermarkets-of-kenya-full-year-profit-falls-55-as-costs-increase.html
Uchumi Supermarkets Ltd.,  Kenya ’s
only publicly traded retailer, said full-year profit fell 55
percent as costs and taxes increased.  Net income dropped to 390.4 million shillings ($4.16
million) in the 12 months through June, from 865.1 million
shillings a year earlier, the Nairobi-based company said in a
statement published in the Daily Nation newspaper today. Revenue
grew 12 percent to 10.8 billion shillings, it said.  “It is expected that the business shall continue to grow
more robustly in the coming year and beyond as we position
ourselves strategically in new locations within the greater East
African region,” the company said.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Paul Richardson at 
 pmrichardson@bloomberg.net  